sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Agent as Autonomous Agent
    participant Root as Root Directory
    participant CWD as Current Working Dir ($CWD)
    participant Skills as Skill Catalog
    participant Context as Dynamic Context

    Note over Agent,Root: 1. Mandatory Core Initialization (Booting Sequence)
    Note right of Agent: This sequence MUST be followed upon every activation.
    Agent->>Root: Read /AGENTS.md (Must)
    Agent->>Root: Read /FLOWS.mmd (Must)
    Agent->>Root: Read /AGENTS.mmd (Must)
    
    Note over Agent,CWD: 2. Directory-Specific Context
    opt When operating inside sub-directories
        Agent->>CWD: Read $CWD/AGENTS.md (When relevant)
        Agent->>CWD: Read $CWD/FLOWS.mmd (When relevant)
        Agent->>CWD: Read $CWD/AGENTS.mmd (When relevant)
    end
    
    Note over Agent,Root: 3. Project Fundamentals
    Agent->>Root: Read README.md (Project overview)
    
    opt When deeper domain knowledge is needed
        Agent->>Root: Read docs/* (Optional)
    end
    
    Note over Agent,Skills: 4. Task-Specific Skill Loading
    opt When task matches skill catalog
        Agent->>Skills: Dynamically load relevant SKILL.md files
    end
    
    Note over Agent,Context: 5. Pattern & Query Specifics
    opt When working with pattern matching files
        Agent->>Context: MUST load specific instructions files (e.g., .instructions.md)
    end
    
    opt When requested by relevant user queries
        Agent->>Context: Load specific prompts/context
    end
